751 /******************************************************************************/
752 /* Peripheral Registers_Bits_Definition */
753 /******************************************************************************/
754 
755 /******************************************************************************/
756 /* */
757 /* CRC calculation unit (CRC) */
758 /* */
759 /******************************************************************************/
760 
761 /******************* Bit definition for CRC_DR register *********************/
762 #define CRC_DR_DR_Pos (0U)
763 #define CRC_DR_DR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFU << CRC_DR_DR_Pos)
764 #define CRC_DR_DR CRC_DR_DR_Msk
766 /******************* Bit definition for CRC_IDR register ********************/
767 #define CRC_IDR_IDR_Pos (0U)
768 #define CRC_IDR_IDR_Msk (0xFFU << CRC_IDR_IDR_Pos)
769 #define CRC_IDR_IDR CRC_IDR_IDR_Msk
771 /******************** Bit definition for CRC_CR register ********************/
772 #define CRC_CR_RESET_Pos (0U)
773 #define CRC_CR_RESET_Msk (0x1U << CRC_CR_RESET_Pos)
774 #define CRC_CR_RESET CRC_CR_RESET_Msk
776 /******************************************************************************/
777 /* */
778 /* Power Control */
779 /* */
780 /******************************************************************************/
781 
782 /******************** Bit definition for PWR_CR register ********************/
783 #define PWR_CR_LPDS_Pos (0U)
784 #define PWR_CR_LPDS_Msk (0x1U << PWR_CR_LPDS_Pos)
785 #define PWR_CR_LPDS PWR_CR_LPDS_Msk
786 #define PWR_CR_PDDS_Pos (1U)
787 #define PWR_CR_PDDS_Msk (0x1U << PWR_CR_PDDS_Pos)
788 #define PWR_CR_PDDS PWR_CR_PDDS_Msk
789 #define PWR_CR_CWUF_Pos (2U)
790 #define PWR_CR_CWUF_Msk (0x1U << PWR_CR_CWUF_Pos)
791 #define PWR_CR_CWUF PWR_CR_CWUF_Msk
792 #define PWR_CR_CSBF_Pos (3U)
793 #define PWR_CR_CSBF_Msk (0x1U << PWR_CR_CSBF_Pos)
794 #define PWR_CR_CSBF PWR_CR_CSBF_Msk
795 #define PWR_CR_PVDE_Pos (4U)
796 #define PWR_CR_PVDE_Msk (0x1U << PWR_CR_PVDE_Pos)
797 #define PWR_CR_PVDE PWR_CR_PVDE_Msk
799 #define PWR_CR_PLS_Pos (5U)
800 #define PWR_CR_PLS_Msk (0x7U << PWR_CR_PLS_Pos)
801 #define PWR_CR_PLS PWR_CR_PLS_Msk
802 #define PWR_CR_PLS_0 (0x1U << PWR_CR_PLS_Pos)
803 #define PWR_CR_PLS_1 (0x2U << PWR_CR_PLS_Pos)
804 #define PWR_CR_PLS_2 (0x4U << PWR_CR_PLS_Pos)
807 #define PWR_CR_PLS_LEV0 0x00000000U
808 #define PWR_CR_PLS_LEV1 0x00000020U
809 #define PWR_CR_PLS_LEV2 0x00000040U
810 #define PWR_CR_PLS_LEV3 0x00000060U

10581 /******************************************************************************/
10582 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F1xx device product */
10583 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
10584 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
10585 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
10586 /* product lines within the same STM32F1 Family */
10587 /******************************************************************************/
10588
